# Progress Notification - MANDATORY

After completing any meaningful progress on the rentApplication project, send a summary email to **natovichat@gmail.com**.

## When to Send

Send after:
- Completing a feature, user story, or epic milestone
- Fixing a bug or resolving an issue
- Finishing a refactor or code improvement
- Completing a test run or QA cycle
- Any other notable progress in a session

## How to Send

Use `send_email.py` with a brief summary of what was accomplished:

```bash
python3 /Users/aviad.natovich/Code/Tasks/Tools/send_email.py \
  --subject "rentApplication Progress: [Short Title]" \
  --body "[What was done - 2-3 sentences max]" \
  --to "natovichat@gmail.com"
```

## Example

```bash
python3 /Users/aviad.natovich/Code/Tasks/Tools/send_email.py \
  --subject "rentApplication Progress: Property list filtering added" \
  --body "Implemented server-side filtering for the property list page. Added query params for address, status, and owner. All unit tests pass." \
  --to "natovichat@gmail.com"
```

## Notes

- Keep the body concise (2-3 sentences max)
- Subject should start with `rentApplication Progress:`
- Send once per meaningful session milestone, not after every small edit
